<h1>Yukihiro Matsumoto</h1>
<p>Yukihiro Matsumoto (まつもとゆきひろ Matsumoto Yukihiro, a.k.a. Matz, born 14 April 1965) is a Japanese computer scientist and software
  programmer best known as the chief designer of the Ruby programming language and its reference implementation, Matz's Ruby
  Interpreter (MRI). His demeanor has brought about a motto in the Ruby community: "Matz is nice and so we are nice," commonly
  abbreviated as MINASWAN.As of 2011, Matsumoto is the Chief Architect of Ruby at Heroku, an online cloud platform-as-a-service
  in San Francisco. He is a fellow of Rakuten Institute of Technology, a research and development organisation in Rakuten
  Inc. He was appointed to the role of technical advisor for VASILY, Inc. starting in June 2014.</p>

